NORTH West police in Potchefstroom are seeking the assistance of public members in identifying three persons of interest in a robbery case. According to Colonel Adéle Myburgh, the Sesotho-speaking suspects are aged between 19 and 37. Myburgh said the suspects could assist cops in a robbery case that was reported at midday on Tuesday, 17 January, in an open field close to Wallis Street. REGISTER TO COMMENT! “During the incident, two pupils were allegedly walking when they were overpowered by suspects and threatened with knives. They were robbed of their cellphones, cash and carry bags containing personal documents,” Myburgh said in a statement. She urged anyone who could assist in identifying them to contact Sergeant Victor Gabaekangoe on 082 378 2890/018 299 7436 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111.